  "text": "The amount of knowledge required for segmentation and extraction of features in layers V 1 and V 2 is low, while the amount of knowledge required for interpreting the image in the semantic layers MI 1 to MI 4 increases. Most automatic image annotation methods are generative or discriminative models [CITATION_1] and work with image interpretation at layers MI 1 and MI 2 . For image interpretation at layers MI 3 and MI 4 knowledge representation models and a reasoning engine are needed.",
